{"parentUuid":"40734530-7935-4a26-8d26-64c8a9aed0c2","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a62a4b9fae3247ab0","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcpzGt5FhANQ381upT4RK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BMSuwLUE7ZHHh1xNKqZ4Ra","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\requirements.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5450,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20875,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20875,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcpzGriPyuMgWSYpzpCjC","attributionAgent":"planning","type":"assistant","uuid":"d96a9a12-38a6-4ea9-8a5e-0d44e9786511","timestamp":"2026-07-08T17:31:05.515Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"d96a9a12-38a6-4ea9-8a5e-0d44e9786511","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"baf21a5c-1a23-429e-9e74-122628363a90","agentId":"a62a4b9fae3247ab0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BMSuwLUE7ZHHh1xNKqZ4Ra","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Requirements — per-customer metric quotas\n2\t\n3\tElicited 2026-07-08 (operator interview, requirements-elicitation first live run).\n4\tBrief: PROJECT.md (PUT /v1/quotas admin-scoped; POST /v1/events 429s on would-exceed;\n5\tone expand-only migration; existing p95 < 50 ms budget on POST /v1/events; no design source).\n6\t\n7\t## Resolved\n8\t\n9\t- What window is `limit_per_window`? → The existing UTC hour rollup window\n10\t  (`floor_to_hour_utc` / rollup `window_start`). The quota check reads the current-hour\n11\t  rollup; no new aggregation.\n12\t- How is a quota tenant-scoped? → Per tenant: `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`.\n13\t  Quota rows carry the tenant key like every other table; an admin key sets quotas for\n14\t  its own tenant's customers only.\n15\t- What does \"would exceed\" mean at the boundary (rollup R, incoming quantity Q, limit L)?\n16\t  → Reject when `R + Q > L`; usage never exceeds L. An event with Q > L against an empty\n17\t  window is rejected too.\n18\t- Throttle-vs-quota precedence on POST /v1/events, and error code? → Tier-2 token-bucket\n19\t  throttle stays first (pre-handler dependency, protects the DB from quota-check load);\n20\t  quota rejections are a distinct envelope `code: quota_exceeded` (429). Existing\n21\t  throttle keeps `code: rate_limited`.\n22\t- How does a key become admin-scoped? → New `scope` column on `api_keys` (default\n23\t  `'ingest'`, expand-only), `scripts/seed_api_key.py` grows an `--admin` flag, the\n24\t  authenticated principal carries the scope, PUT /v1/quotas requires `scope = 'admin'`\n25\t  (403 `forbidden` otherwise).\n26\t- PUT /v1/quotas semantics for an existing row? → Upsert: create-or-replace\n27\t  `(customer_id, metric) → limit_per_window` (201 create / 200 replace); response body\n28\t  echoes the stored quota. No removal path this slice.\n29\t- When does a quota set/changed mid-window take effect? → Immediately, against the\n30\t  current window's already-accumulated rollup. Lowering L below current R blocks the\n31\t  rest of the window.\n32\t- Concurrent POSTs racing at the quota edge? → Strict enforcement: the quota check is\n33\t  atomic with the rollup increment inside the existing per-request transaction (guarding\n34\t  the rollup row, e.g. row lock / conditional update), so usage can never exceed L.\n35\t  Serializes concurrent posts on the same (customer, metric, window) row; the p95\n36\t  < 50 ms budget still applies.\n37\t- Idempotent replay (duplicate idempotency_key) when the window is now over quota? →\n38\t  200 replay with the original stored result; the quota is not consulted. The\n39\t  idempotency contract is absolute — a retry of an accepted event never flips to 429,\n40\t  and a replay adds no usage.\n41\t- Validation bounds on `limit_per_window`? → Integer >= 1 only; 0 and negatives are\n42\t  rejected 422 (`validation_failed`). A quota is a cap, not a kill switch.\n43\t- Extra contents of the 429 quota response? → `Retry-After` header = seconds until the\n44\t  next hour window (matches the throttle's existing header pattern). Body stays the\n45\t  standard three-field envelope `{code, message, requestId}` — no usage numbers in\n46\t  error bodies.\n47\t- The brief's \"ONE expand-only migration\" vs the new api_keys scope column? → One\n48\t  Alembic revision containing both expand-only changes: CREATE TABLE quotas + ALTER\n49\t  TABLE api_keys ADD COLUMN scope DEFAULT 'ingest' (backfill-free).\n50\t- Is PUT /v1/quotas behind the normal edge stack? → Yes: require_api_key → Tier-2\n51\t  per-key throttle → scope check (403) → handler. No admin special-casing.\n52\t- Data classification of the new stored fields (customer_id, metric, limit_per_window,\n53\t  scope)? → Non-sensitive operational config; customer_id/metric are opaque\n54\t  tenant-scoped identifiers already stored in events/rollups. Storage-level encryption\n55\t  (RDS SSE) suffices; no field-level crypto.\n56\t\n57\t## Open\n58\t\n59\t- Latency budget for PUT /v1/quotas itself — not discussed in the interview; the stated\n60\t  p95 < 50 ms budget applies to POST /v1/events only. Planning should either state a\n61\t  sensible default for the (low-traffic, admin-only) route or raise it at the plan\n62\t  checkpoint.\n63\t\n64\t## Out of scope\n65\t\n66\t- Removing/unsetting a quota (DELETE /v1/quotas or `limit: null`) — customers go back\n67\t  to unlimited only via direct DB change this slice.\n68\t- GET /v1/quotas (read/list endpoint) — the PUT response echo is the only read.\n69\t- `limit_per_window = 0` as a customer/metric kill switch — blocking a customer\n70\t  outright is a different feature.\n71\t- Global / cross-tenant quotas — quotas are per (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) only.\n72\t- Deferred effectiveness (`effective_from` / next-window-only quota changes) — changes\n73\t  apply immediately.\n74\t- Usage/limit/window-reset detail in the 429 error body.\n75\t- Daily or per-quota-configurable windows — hour windows only.\n76\t- Any change of behavior for customers without a quota row (they stay unlimited).\n77\t"}]},"uuid":"fa2dc4dd-149e-443f-b3a5-548027fc6aa7","timestamp":"2026-07-08T17:31:05.538Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d96a9a12-38a6-4ea9-8a5e-0d44e9786511","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
