{"parentUuid":"b0ee9e05-3596-4be5-ada2-6ac7234443ef","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"baf21a5c-1a23-429e-9e74-122628363a90","agentId":"a62a4b9fae3247ab0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018VcVfsRPPsNnm9UjzouEZa","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tFeature: per-customer metric quotas.\n2\t- PUT /v1/quotas (admin-scoped API key) sets {customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}.\n3\t- POST /v1/events returns 429 with a quota error envelope when the current-window rollup for that customer/metric would exceed the quota. Customers without a quota are unlimited (no behavior change).\n4\t- One expand-only migration: a quotas table.\n5\t- Existing perf budget applies: p95 < 50 ms under load on POST /v1/events.\n6\tDesign source: none.\n7\t"}]},"uuid":"18ec5d63-95c6-4d39-b89d-eb4aea98ce68","timestamp":"2026-07-08T17:31:05.849Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b0ee9e05-3596-4be5-ada2-6ac7234443ef","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
